{
  "texts": [
    "Possessing SRL skills equips a student with the ability to monitor their behavior in alignment with their goals and to self-reflect on their growing effectiveness.",
    "This self-monitoring and reflection are key to success, as they enhance the learners' ability to adapt and improve their strategies over time (Zimmerman, 2002).",
    "To evolve into a self-regulated learner, an individual needs to cultivate the key processes: cognition, metacognition, and motivation (Ifenthaler, 2012; Lehmann & I. Hähnlein et al., 2014; Zimmerman, 2002).",
    "Cognition is the mental act of acquiring knowledge and understanding (Ifenthaler, 2012; Zimmerman, 2002).",
    "It encompasses processes like thinking, knowing, remembering, judging, and problem-solving."
  ]
}